---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../../components/shared/Container.astro';
import MonoEyebrow from '../../components/shared/MonoEyebrow.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions — Blue Business"
  description="General terms and conditions of Blue Innovation B.V. (Blue Business), version 2021. Registered with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce under number 80387578."
  canonicalPath="/en/terms/"
>
  <section class="pt-[140px] md:pt-[180px] pb-10">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <MonoEyebrow text="// Legal" tone="accent-hi" class="mb-5 block" />
      <h1 class="text-h1 font-medium" style="letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight); line-height: 1.02;">
        <span class="block text-fg">Terms &</span>
        <span class="block text-accent">Conditions.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body text-fg-dim mt-6 max-w-[60ch]">
        Blue Innovation B.V., version 2021. Registered with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce under number 80387578, with registered office at Rietsingel 46, 2136 LB Zwaanshoek.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-[10px] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/[0.06] border border-[var(--color-accent-line)] max-w-[60ch]">
        <p class="text-[14px] text-fg-dim">
          This is an informational English summary. The legally binding version is the Dutch Algemene Voorwaarden. <a href="/nl/voorwaarden/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">Read the Dutch version</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-24">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <div class="space-y-6 text-[15px] text-fg-dim" style="line-height: 1.7;">
        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Applicability</h2>
        <p>
          These terms and conditions apply to every offer from Blue Innovation and to every distance contract between Blue Innovation and the Client. Before a distance contract is concluded, the text of these terms and conditions is made available to the Client. Any general terms and conditions of Clients and/or third parties do not apply to the agreement between the Client and Blue Innovation. Rights and obligations under the Agreement may not be transferred by the Client to a third party without Blue Innovation's express prior consent.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Offers and quotes</h2>
        <p>
          All offers and quotes made by Blue Innovation are non-binding, unless otherwise agreed in writing, and are valid for 14 days. A quote applies only to the specific assignment and does not guarantee the same price for future quotes. The offer contains a complete and accurate description of the offered products and/or services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">The agreement</h2>
        <p>
          The agreement is concluded when the Client indicates assent by accepting the offer, paying the amount, or accepting the assignment in writing. If the Client accepts the offer electronically, Blue Innovation will immediately confirm receipt of the acceptance electronically. Until receipt of this acceptance is confirmed, the Client may rescind the agreement free of charge.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Right of withdrawal</h2>
        <p>
          When purchasing products, the Consumer has the right to dissolve the agreement without giving reasons within 14 days. This period begins on the day the Consumer or a designated representative receives the product. If a Consumer invokes the right of withdrawal, Blue Innovation is entitled to charge the costs incurred up to that point. A Business that has entered into a software subscription with Blue Innovation does not have the right to withdraw from this agreement.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Performance of the agreement</h2>
        <p>
          Blue Innovation will endeavor to perform the Agreement with the greatest possible care as expected of a good contractor. All Services are performed on a best-efforts basis, unless a specific, detailed result has been expressly agreed in writing. Blue Innovation is entitled to engage third parties at its own discretion for the performance of the Services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Access to the SaaS service</h2>
        <p>
          Blue Innovation only offers the use of the SaaS service, including the Website and Mobile app. Blue Innovation has no responsibility for or influence over the actual operation of the Client's business. Blue Innovation reserves the right to deny the Client access to the SaaS service and/or to terminate use of the SaaS service in case of misuse and/or possible criminal acts. Blue Innovation is free to perform maintenance on the SaaS service, Website and Mobile app, and to take them out of service as a result.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          Blue Innovation performs the Services in accordance with industry standards. Any warranty is limited to what is expressly agreed in writing. The Client can only invoke the warranty if the Client has fully met its payment obligations. Blue Innovation does not warrant that the Website and/or Mobile app will function without errors or interruptions. The Client accepts the Website and Mobile app "AS IS".
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Right of use and usage restrictions</h2>
        <p>
          Blue Innovation provides the agreed Bluebusiness software and user documentation to the Client on a license basis for the duration of the Agreement. The Client may use the Bluebusiness software only in and for its own business, and exclusively for the intended purpose. The Client may never sell, rent, transfer, or grant limited rights on the Bluebusiness software, nor provide it to a third party.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Force majeure</h2>
        <p>
          Blue Innovation is not liable when it cannot fulfill its obligations under the Agreement due to a force majeure situation. Force majeure includes, but is not limited to: force majeure at suppliers, failure of third-party suppliers to perform, defects in third-party goods, government measures, power outages, internet/telecom failures (cybercrime, hacking, DDoS), natural disasters, war and terrorism. If force majeure lasts longer than two months, either Party may rescind the Agreement in writing.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          If performance of Services leads to liability on the part of Blue Innovation, that liability is limited to the costs charged in connection with the SaaS service (maximum 6 months preceding the notice of default) for direct damage. Blue Innovation is not liable for consequential damage, indirect damage, business losses, lost profits, loss of data, delay damage or interest damage. All claims of the Client for shortcomings lapse if not reported in writing and substantiated to Blue Innovation within one year.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          All intellectual property rights of Blue Innovation, including the SaaS service, Website, Mobile app, data files, Bluebusiness software, designs, analyses and documentation, belong exclusively to Blue Innovation. The Client may not disclose, reproduce, modify or provide to third parties any component of the SaaS service, Website, Mobile app or Bluebusiness software on which Blue Innovation's IP rights rest, without prior written consent. Each infringement by the Client is subject to a one-time penalty of €10,000 plus €500 for each day the infringement continues.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Price and payment</h2>
        <p>
          Prices in the offer are exclusive of VAT. The Client must pay within the agreed terms on the invoice. If the Client fails to pay on time, the Client is in default by operation of law after a reminder is sent. The Client is then owed statutory interest (consumer) or statutory commercial interest (business) plus 1%. Extrajudicial collection costs are calculated with a minimum of €40 and a maximum of €6,775.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Termination</h2>
        <p>
          The Client may terminate the agreement at any desired moment with one month's notice, effective at the beginning of the month. If the Client terminates, the Client will no longer have access to the software as of the end date.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Complaints</h2>
        <p>
          Blue Innovation has a sufficiently publicized complaints procedure and handles complaints in accordance with it. Complaints about the performance of the agreement must be submitted to Blue Innovation in full and clearly described within 7 days of receipt of the product. Submitted complaints are answered within 14 days. The Client must give Blue Innovation at least 4 weeks to resolve the complaint by mutual agreement.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Applicable law</h2>
        <p>
          Dutch law applies to all agreements, services, offers and orders. Any disputes must be submitted to the competent court in the Netherlands.
        </p>

        <p class="pt-6 font-mono text-[12px] text-fg-faint">Zwaanshoek, August 2021.</p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
